articles.title: Japan stocks lead gains in Asia with Nikkei hitting fresh 34-year highs; Singapore budget on tap - CNBC
articles.description: Japan's Nikkei 225 was on course to reach all-time highs — it was less than 100 points from scaling its record peak at its intraday high of 38,863.6
articles.content:
Hong Kong markets led gains in Asia on Friday, with Japan's Nikkei 225 hitting a fresh 34-year high as it attempted to scale its all-time peak.
